<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-16T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-16T15:00:00-05:00" n="770" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/271: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jay</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-16T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            16, 1920—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>25. Department’s May 20, 6 p.m., 1919,<note n="88" xml:id="d770fn88"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_671"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1919, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                                        p. 671</ref>.</note> and November 28, 2 p.m., 1919.<note n="89" xml:id="d770fn89"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_673"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 673</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>It is desired that you report by telegraph what if any
                                representations were made by you to the Italian Government and the
                                results thereof.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>